Outside Emporium Alani
You're standing in front of the Giorgio Alani Emporium entrance. Two
large brass doors await northward your entrance into the sanctuary of
fashion consumism.

> ; ******************************************************************************
> ; *                                                                            *
> ; *                          TEST NEW CLOTHING SYSTEM                          *
> ; *                                                                            *
> ; ******************************************************************************
> ; This script is designed to test the development of the new clothing system,
> ; which doesn't use the 'worn' entity any more to store clothes worn by Hero.
> north
As you move toward the doors they automagically slide open before you.

Emporium Alani Main Hall
This luxurious hall is the crossroad to the various clothing departments
of the emporium. Two large brass doors lead the way south, out of the
fashion temple and back into the world of mortal souls.There is your
personal assistant here.

> ; ==============================================================================
> ; CLOTHING INITIALIZATION
> ; ==============================================================================
> ; Let's check that clothes have been properly initialized by the library.
> ; In the source adventure, worn items are places IN the wearing actor and set as
> ; 'IS donned', the library then takes care of adding them to the 'wearing' set.
> ; ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
> ; HERO'S CLOTHING -> OK!
> ; ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
> inventory
You are empty-handed. You are wearing your socks, your boxers, your 
undershirt, your sneakers and your khakis.

> DBG sneakers
'sneakers' VALUES: | feetcover: 4 | 
DONNED: Yes 
IN WORN: No. 
IN WEARING OF: | hero

> DBG boxers
'boxers' VALUES: | botcover: 2 | 
DONNED: Yes 
IN WORN: No. 
IN WEARING OF: | hero

> DBG socks
'socks' VALUES: | feetcover: 2 | 
DONNED: Yes 
IN WORN: No. 
IN WEARING OF: | hero

> ; ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
> ; NPC CLOTHING  -> OK!
> ; ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
> examine assistant
She's your personal shopping assistant. The assistant is carrying a 
prices list. The assistant is wearing a uniform and a pair of fashion
boots.

> DBG boots
'fashion boots' VALUES: | feetcover: 4 | 
DONNED: Yes 
IN WORN: No. 
IN WEARING OF: | assistant

> DBG uniform
'uniform' VALUES: | topcover: 8 | botcover: 32 | 
DONNED: Yes 
IN WORN: No. 
IN WEARING OF: | assistant

> ; ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
> ; NESTED CLOTHING AND OBJECTS -> OK!
> ; ------------------------------------------------------------------------------
> ; Let's check that clothing items inside worn clothes are seen as being just
> ; carried, not worn. Previously the library would mark as 'donned' any object
> ; inside a worn item.
> examine khakis
A pair of khaki beige cotton pants. Inside the khakis pockets there are 
your kippah and your wallet.

> DBG khakis
'khakis' VALUES: | botcover: 16 | 
DONNED: Yes 
IN WORN: No. 
IN WEARING OF: | hero

> ; The kippah shouldn't be 'donned' nor in 'wearing' of Hero:
> DBG kippah
'kippah' VALUES: (none) 
DONNED: No. 
IN WORN: No. 
IN WEARING OF:

